Calculator&rdquo;, National Physical Laboratory Report, in Copeland
2005: 369&ndash;454 (ch. 20).
doi:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780198565932.003.0021</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1947 [2004], &ldquo;Lecture on the
Automatic Computing Engine&rdquo;, London Mathematical Society, in
Copeland 2004: 378&ndash;394 (ch. 9).</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1948 [2004], &ldquo;Intelligent
Machinery&rdquo;, National Physical Laboratory Report, in Copeland
2004: 410&ndash;432 (ch. 10).</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1950a [2004], &ldquo;Computing Machinery
and Intelligence&rdquo;, <em>Mind</em>, 59(236): 433&ndash;460.
Reprinted in Copeland 2004: 441&ndash;464 (ch. 11).
doi:10.1093/mind/LIX.236.433</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1950b, &ldquo;The Word Problem in
Semi-Groups With Cancellation&rdquo;, <em>Annals of Mathematics</em>,
second series 52(2): 491&ndash;505. doi:10.2307/1969481</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, c.1950, <em>Programmers&rsquo; Handbook for
Manchester Electronic Computer Mark II</em>, Computing Machine
Laboratory, University of Manchester.
 [<a href="http://www.AlanTuring.net/programmers_handbook" target="other">Turing c.1950 available online</a>]</li>
 
<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1954 [2004], &ldquo;Solvable and Unsolvable
Problems&rdquo;, <em>Science News</em> (Penguin Books), 31:
7&ndash;23. Reprinted in Copeland 2004: 582&ndash;595 (ch. 17).</li>

<li>van Heijenoort, Jean, 1967, <em>From Frege to G&ouml;del: A Source
Book in Mathematical Logic, 1879&ndash;1931</em>, Cambridge, MA:
Harvard University Press.</li>

<li>Venn, John, 1880, &ldquo;On the Diagrammatic and Mechanical
Representation of Propositions and Reasonings&rdquo;, <em>The London,
Edinburgh, and Dublin Philosophical Magazine and Journal of
Science</em>, fifth series, 10(59): 1&ndash;18.
doi:10.1080/14786448008626877</li>

<li>von Neumann, John, 1927, &ldquo;Zur Hilbertschen
Beweistheorie&rdquo;, <em>Mathematische Zeitschrift</em>, 26(1):
1&ndash;46. doi:10.1007/BF01475439</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1931, &ldquo;Die formalistische Grundlegung
der Mathematik&rdquo;, <em>Erkenntnis</em>, 2(1): 116&ndash;121.
doi:10.1007/BF02028144</li>

<li>Wang, Hao, 1974, <em>From Mathematics to Philosophy</em>, New
York: Humanities Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1996, <em>A Logical Journey: From
G&ouml;del to Philosophy</em>, Cambridge, MA: MIT Press.</li>

<li>Weyl, Hermann, 1927 [1949], &ldquo;Philosophie der Mathematik und
Naturwissenschaft&rdquo;, <em>Handbuch der Philosophie</em>, Munich:
Oldenbourg. Published in English as <em>Philosophy of Mathematics and
Natural Science</em>, Princeton, NJ: Princeton University Press,
1949.</li>

<li>Wittgenstein, Ludwig, 1947 [1980], <em>Bemerkungen &uuml;ber die
Philosophie der Psychologie</em>. Translated as <em>Remarks on the
Philosophy of Psychology</em>, Volume 1, Anscombe, G. Elizabeth M. and
Georg Henrik von Wright (eds), Oxford: Blackwell, 1980.</li>

<li>Wolfram, Stephen, 1985, &ldquo;Undecidability and Intractability
in Theoretical Physics&rdquo;, <em>Physical Review Letters</em>,
54(8): 735&ndash;738. doi:10.1103/PhysRevLett.54.735</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2021, <em>Combinators: A Centennial
View</em>, Champaign, IL: Wolfram Media.</li>

<li>Yao, Andrew C.-C., 2003, &ldquo;Classical Physics and the
Church-Turing Thesis&rdquo;, <em>Journal of the ACM</em>, 50(1):
100&ndash;105. doi:10.1145/602382.602411</li>

<li>Zach, Richard, 1999, &ldquo;Completeness Before Post: Bernays,
Hilbert, and the Development of Propositional Logic&rdquo;,
<em>Bulletin of Symbolic Logic</em>, 5(3): 331&ndash;366.
doi:10.2307/421184</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2003, &ldquo;The Practice of Finitism:
Epsilon Calculus and Consistency Proofs in Hilbert&rsquo;s
Program&rdquo;, <em>Synthese</em>, 137(1/2): 211&ndash;259.
doi:10.1023/A:1026247421383</li>

<li>Zanichelli, Nicola (ed.), 1929, <em>Atti del Congresso
Internazionale dei Matematici, Bologna, 3&ndash;10 Settembre 1928,
Volume 1: Rendiconto del Congresso Conferenze</em>, Bologna:
Societ&agrave; Tipografica.</li>
</ul>
</div> 

